You are executing the /deploy skill for the Builds workspace.

## Purpose
Deploy code changes to EC2 and verify the service is healthy after restart.
Only one deployable target exists: Rapid2 v1.2 (the live production bot).
Rapid2 v1 was retired 2026-03-04 — its EC2 instance is terminated.

---

## Step 1 — Confirm the target

If the user didn't specify, confirm:
"Deploying Rapid2 v1.2 to EC2 (live trading bot — real money). The service will restart briefly. Confirm?"

**DO NOT SKIP** — Wait for explicit confirmation before proceeding.

---

## Step 2 — Show what will be deployed

Run `git diff --name-only HEAD` (or `git status`) in the project folder.
Present as: "These files will be deployed: [list]"

Do NOT proceed if the list is empty or unexpected.

---

## Step 3 — Deploy

```
Local path:  c:\Users\benja\OneDrive\Documents\Builds\Rapid2\rapid2 v1.2\
EC2 path:    rapid2:/home/ubuntu/rapid2-v1.2/
Service:     openclaw-paper.service
SSH alias:   rapid2
```

Files to deploy (only changed Python/config files — never .env):
- `bot.py`, `strategy.py`, `paper_bot.py` (if changed)
- Do NOT deploy: `.env`, `state/`, `.git/`

```bash
scp <changed_files> rapid2:/home/ubuntu/rapid2-v1.2/
ssh rapid2 "sudo systemctl restart openclaw-paper.service"
```

---

## Step 4 — Tag the deploy in git

```bash
cd "c:/Users/benja/OneDrive/Documents/Builds/Rapid2/rapid2 v1.2"
git tag deploy-$(date +%Y-%m-%d-%H%M)
```

This creates a marker like `deploy-2026-03-01-0715` that /rollback uses to restore
the last known-good version. Skip if the working tree is dirty; note it in the summary.

---

## Step 5 — Verify health

After restart, wait 4 seconds then:
1. Check `systemctl is-active openclaw-paper.service` — must return `active`
2. Show last 15 log lines via `journalctl -u openclaw-paper.service --no-pager -n 15`
3. Confirm: "Deploy successful — bot is running" or report the error

If the service failed to start, show the full error and offer to run /rollback immediately.
